## AIOS dual-model review

**Verdict:** approve | request changes | comment-only

**Summary.** One sentence — what the PR does and whether it is safe to merge.

### Blockers
- (only items both reviewers raised, OR one reviewer raised and the other
  did not contradict). Cite file:line. Empty list = no blockers.

### Suggestions
- non-blocking improvements consolidated from both reviews. Dedupe.

### Risks the PR did not name
- consolidated; one bullet per risk.

### Test gaps
- consolidated; one bullet per gap.

### Reviewer disagreements
- list any specific point where A and B disagreed, naming which side took
  which position. Empty list = no disagreements.

Rules:
- The verdict is the most conservative of the two: if either reviewer said
  request-changes, the merged verdict is request-changes.
- If a blocker appears in only one review and the other did not address
  it, demote it to "Suggestions" or to "Reviewer disagreements" with
  attribution.
- Do not invent issues neither reviewer raised.
- Do not write a "summary of the changes" paragraph beyond the one-sentence
  Summary above.
